\[\tan x = \frac{9 \pm \sqrt{77}}{2}.\]Let $r_1 = \frac{9 + \sqrt{77}}{2}$ and $r_2 = \frac{9 - \sqrt{77}}{2}.$  Note that $r_1 r_2 = 1.$

Graphing $y = \tan x,$ we see that $\tan x = r_1$ for two angles in $[0,2 \pi],$ and $\tan x = r_2$ for two angles in $[0,2 \pi].$

